-- Greece to auction 625 mln euros of 6-month T-bills on Feb 4
-- 
-- Fri Jan 31, 2014 06:35AM EST
-- None



ATHENS, Jan 31 (Reuters) - Greece will auction 625 million euros ($847.72 million) of six-month treasury bills on February 4 to refinance a maturing issue, the country's debt agency PDMA said on Friday.

The settlement date will be February 7. Only primary dealers will be allowed to participate and no commission will be paid.